Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of web accessibility tests.

Ten different tools (Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE) tested the web page of Scott D. Wiener (D) at https://sd11.senate.ca.gov/ to check its compliance with various rules. There were a total of about 1350 rules, classified into about 250 accessibility issues.

The results were interpreted to yield an aggregate score of 1950, where 0 would be perfect.

Total score

The total score is the sum of five components.

Score summary
ComponentScoreDescription
total1950Sum of the component scores
issue1409Severity and number of reported defects
tool211Tool-by-tool defect ratings
prevention300Failed attempts by tools to test the page
log30Browser warnings about the page
latency0Abnormal delay in page responses

Issue scores

The score of an issue depends on the severity (user impact and certainty) of the issue and on how many instances were reported (by one or more tools).

Itemized issues

The reported rule violations are itemized below, issue by issue. Additional details can be inspected in the complete report at the end of this page.

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 284

Complaints by alfa

Rule r69

Description: Text outside widget has subminimum contrast

Count of instances: 71

Complaint specifics
  • Text outside widget has minimum contrast

Complaints by axe

Rule color-contrast

Description: Element has insufficient color contrast

Count of instances: 27

Complaint specifics
  • Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds; Element's background color could not be determined because element contains an image node
  • Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds; Element has a 1:1 contrast ratio with the background
  • Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds; Element's background color could not be determined due to a background image
  • Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds; Element has insufficient color contrast of 3.38 (foreground color: #ffffff, background color: #e06911, font size: 10.5pt (14px), font weight: bold). Expected contrast ratio of 4.5:1
  • Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds; Element has insufficient color contrast of 2.87 (foreground color: #e06911, background color: #0f4480, font size: 10.5pt (14px), font weight: bold). Expected contrast ratio of 4.5:1

Complaints by ibm

Rule text_contrast_sufficient

Description: Text has a contrast with its background less than the WCAG AA minimum for its size and weight

Count of instances: 10

Complaint specifics
  • Text contrast of 3.39 with its background is less than the WCAG AA minimum requirements for text of size 16px and weight of 700
  • Text contrast of 2.87 with its background is less than the WCAG AA minimum requirements for text of size 16px and weight of 700

Complaints by qualWeb

Rule QW-ACT-R37

Description: Text has less than the minimum contrast

Count of instances: 7

Complaint specifics
  • This rule checks that the highest possible contrast of every text character with its background meets the minimal contrast requirement.

Complaints by wave

Rule contrast

Description: Very low contrast

Count of instances: 20

Complaint specifics
  • Very low contrast
